Hang Seng China Enterprises Index Down
HONG KONG , December 28 ( Xinhua ) -- Hang Seng China Enterprises Index fell three points to close at 392.16 on Monday .
The Index , introduced in August 1995 , tracks the overall performance of 40 China 's state-owned enterprises listed on the Hong Kong Stock Exchange .
New Hang Seng MidCap50 Index lost 7.16 points from the previous session to close at 757.51
New Hang Seng MidCap 50 Index comprises 50 stocks ranked from 101 to 150 on the Hong Kong bourse in terms of market capitalization and turnover .
Hang Seng China-Affiliated Corporations Index fell 12.22 points to close at 913.38 .
Hang Seng China-Affiliated Corporations Index tracks the performance of 43 locally-listed companies with a significant equity interest held by entities in China .
The three segmented Hang Seng indices are devised by Hang Seng Index ( HSI ) Services Limited , a wholly-owned subsidiary of Hang Seng Bank .
